Documentation and privacy guidelines for the Household Expense Tracker
# Privacy Policy for Household Expense Tracker

Effective Date:** 06.07.2026

BM Digital Solutions built the **Household Expense Tracker** app as a **[Free / Freemium / Ad-Supported / Commercial]** app. This Service is provided by BM Digital Solutions and is intended for use as is.

This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect information when you use the Household Expense Tracker app.

 1. Information Collection and Use
Household Expense Tracker allows users to enter and manage household financial records such as income, expenses, budget details, categories, dates, notes, and payment methods.

The app may collect or store the following information:

Expense records entered by the user
Income and budget details entered by the user
Categories, notes, dates, and payment method details
App usage information
Device information, crash logs, or diagnostic data, if analytics or crash reporting services are used

We do not collect bank passwords, debit card PINs, credit card PINs, OTPs, net banking login details, or any other confidential banking credentials.

2. Local Data Storage

The information entered by users may be stored locally on the user’s device. If the app provides cloud backup, account login, or data sync features, user data may also be stored securely using third-party cloud services.

Users are responsible for maintaining the security of their own device and backup accounts.

3. How We Use Information

We use the information only for app-related purposes, including:

* Tracking household expenses and income
* Creating reports, summaries, and charts
* Helping users manage budgets and savings
* Improving app performance and user experience
* Fixing bugs and technical issues
* Providing backup, restore, or sync features, if available

4. Third-Party Services

The app may use third-party services that may collect information used to identify users or improve app functionality.

These services may include:

* Google Play Services
* Google Firebase
* Google Analytics for Firebase
* Google AdMob
* Firebase Crashlytics

These third-party services have their own privacy policies. Users are encouraged to review their privacy policies for more information.

5. Advertising

If the app displays advertisements, third-party advertising services such as Google AdMob may collect limited device and usage information to show relevant ads and measure ad performance.

Users can manage ad personalization through their device settings or Google account settings.

6. App Permissions

Household Expense Tracker may request certain permissions depending on app features, such as:

* Internet permission, for ads, analytics, cloud backup, or sync features
* Storage permission, if the app allows users to export, import, or back up reports
* Notification permission, if the app provides reminders for expense tracking

These permissions are used only to provide app-related features.

7. Data Sharing

We do not sell, rent, or trade users’ personal information.

User information may be shared only in the following cases:

* When required by law or legal authority
* With trusted third-party service providers used for app functionality
* For analytics, crash reporting, cloud backup, or advertising services
* With the user’s consent

8. Data Security

We value your trust in providing your information. We use reasonable security measures to protect user data from unauthorized access, loss, misuse, or disclosure.

However, no method of electronic storage or transmission over the internet is 100% secure. Therefore, we cannot guarantee absolute security.

9. User Control and Data Deletion

Users can add, edit, or delete their expense records within the app.

Users may also clear app data from their device settings. If the app provides account login, cloud backup, or sync features, users may request deletion of their account and associated data by contacting us.

For data deletion requests, please contact:

Email:[bimalmurmu756@gmail.com](mailto:bimalmurmu756@gmail.com)

10. Children’s Privacy

Household Expense Tracker is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

If we become aware that a child has provided personal information, we will take steps to delete such information.

11. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page or inside the app.

Users are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes. Changes are effective immediately after they are posted.

12. Contact Us

If you have any questions or suggestions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

